, in honor of former Senator Lewis Linn who had advocated for
			 passage of the Donation Land Claim Act that Moore used to establish the
			 town;

text.#text:
Whereas on August 15, 1913, after nearly 75 years as a
			 United States settlement and thousands of years as a sacred home to indigenous
			 peoples, West Linn was incorporated as a city in the State of Oregon;
